[center][size=5][b]SosGui[/b][/size]
[i]An ImGui frontend for SkyrimOutfitSystemSE[/i][/center]

[line]

[size=4][b]Overview[/b][/size]

SkyrimOutfitSystemSE is personally my favourite outfit mod. It perfectly matches what I want from a transmog system: no need to actually own the armor, no dependency on inventory, and safe to uninstall. The only weak point has always been MCM — navigating those menus is slow and cumbersome, and you can never preview armor without leaving the menu entirely.

So I built [b]SosGui[/b]: a fast, immediate-mode UI powered by [url=https://github.com/ocornut/imgui]Dear ImGui[/url] that replaces the MCM workflow entirely. Filter, preview, and batch-edit outfits without ever leaving the panel. Speed is the priority — no transitions, no reloads.

[line]

[size=4][b]Features[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][b]Full feature parity[/b] with SkyrimOutfitSystemSE — everything you could do in MCM, now faster
[*][b]In-menu armor preview[/b] — see how an armor looks without closing the panel
[*][b]Batch operations[/b] — add or remove multiple items at once
[*][b]Fast iteration[/b] — immediate-mode UI with no fade transitions or menu reloads
[*][b]Gamepad support[/b] — standard ImGui gamepad navigation out of the box
[/list]

[size=3][b]Gamepad Controls[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][b]Left Stick / D-Pad[/b] — Navigate between items
[*][b]A[/b] — Activate / Open / Toggle (hold 0.6 s to enter Text Input mode)
[*][b]B[/b] — Cancel / Close / Back up navigation hierarchy
[*][b]X[/b] — Toggle menu / hold for Windowing mode (Focus / Move / Resize)
[*][b]LB[/b] — Tweak slower / Focus previous window (Windowing mode)
[*][b]RB[/b] — Tweak faster / Focus next window (Windowing mode)
[/list]

[line]

[size=4][b]Installation[/b][/size]

[b]Recommended: Mod Organizer 2[/b]

[list=1]
[*]Install [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/skyrimspecialedition/mods/42162]SkyrimOutfitSystemSE Revived[/url] and all of its requirements first.
[*]Download the latest release of SosGui from the Files tab.
[*]Install via Mod Organizer 2 (or your preferred mod manager) as usual.
[*]Enable the mod and ensure it loads [b]after[/b] SkyrimOutfitSystemSE.
[*]Launch the game. A voice spell ([b]SosGuiShow[/b]) will be added to your player automatically on game start.
[/list]

[b]Opening the Menu[/b]

Cast the [b]SosGuiShow[/b] voice spell — the SosGui panel will open immediately. No MCM required.

[line]

[size=4][b]Compatibility[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][b]Requires[/b] [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/skyrimspecialedition/mods/42162]SkyrimOutfitSystemSE Revived[/url] — SosGui is a UI frontend for that mod and cannot function without it.
[*]Compatible with any mod that does not conflict with SkyrimOutfitSystemSE itself.
[*]Should be compatible with ENB, ReShade, and other overlay tools as long as they do not block ImGui DirectX hooks.
[*][b]Not compatible[/b] with other ImGui-based UI mods that hook the same render target if they conflict at the DirectX swap-chain level.
[/list]

[line]

[size=4][b]Requirements[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/skyrimspecialedition/mods/42162][b]SkyrimOutfitSystemSE Revived[/b][/url] — the outfit management system this UI is built on top of
[*][b]Skyrim Special Edition[/b] (Anniversary Edition supported)
[*][b]SKSE64[/b] — required by SkyrimOutfitSystemSE
[/list]

[line]

